    <article class="article PageDW-enJavaScriptReferenceGlobalObjectsMathPI" role="main"><div class="page-title hideforedit">&#13;
              <h1 class="first entry-title roundTop" id="title">Math.PI</h1>            &#13;
      &#13;
              </div>&#13;
      &#13;
    <div class="page-content boxed">&#13;
&#13;
     &#13;
       &#13;
    &#13;
            &#13;
      <div id="page-top"><div class="pageText" id="pageText"><p>
 </p>
<div id="section_1"><span id="Summary"/><h3 class="editable"> Summary </h3>
<p>The ratio of the circumference of a circle to its diameter, approximately 3.14159.
</p>
<table class="standard-table"><thead><tr><th class="header" colspan="2">Property of <a rel="internal" href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Math" title="en/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Math"><code>Math</code></a></th> </tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Implemented in</td> <td>JavaScript 1.0</td> </tr><tr><td>ECMAScript Edition</td> <td>ECMAScript 1st Edition</td> </tr></tbody></table></div><div id="section_2"><span id="Description"/><h3 class="editable"> Description </h3>
<p>Because <code>PI</code> is a static property of <code>Math</code>, you always use it as <code>Math.PI</code>, rather than as a property of a <code>Math</code> object you created.
</p>
</div><div id="section_3"><span id="Examples"/><h3 class="editable"> Examples </h3>
<div id="section_4"><span id="Example:_Using_PI"/><h4 class="editable"> Example: Using <code>PI</code> </h4>
<p>The following function returns the value of pi:
</p>
<pre>
function getPi() {
   return Math.PI
}
</pre> </div></div></div></div>&#13;
